<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUN 94 / Observer: Ex-directory
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
So you want the number for Heathrow airport? Readers of British Telecom's
latest telephone directory are requested to 'see Airports'.
On arrival at this page in the directory, they are re-directed to 'see our
display advertisement'. Then the trail goes cold.
The same fate awaits anyone wanting to discover the number for Gatwick and
Stansted airports. Of course, pay 45p to directory inquiries and the number
is yours for the asking.
</TEXT>
