<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUN 94 / Gas fields contracts awarded
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Amoco UK has awarded contracts worth more than Pounds 46m in the development
of the Davy and Bessemer natural gas fields, which lie about 60 miles off
the East Anglian coast.
The contracts include Pounds 14m to Brown and Root Highland Fabricators for
the construction of two single-leg platforms, the first time such designs
have been used in the North Sea.
Total development costs of the two fields are expected to be about Pounds
160m.
