<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUN 94 / Multiple choice for TV news launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Videotron, the London cable television operator, has joined forces with
Carlton Television and London Weekend Television to produce what is claimed
to be the UK's first daily interactive news service.
The experiment which began yesterday allows Videotron subscribers to choose
between four versions of the main London regional news and magazine
programmes.
In addition to the two main programmes broadcast by the London
franchise-holders, customers will have three other options. They are: a
local weather and traffic service; a compilation programme of all the week's
social-action items; a repeat of After 5 - the early evening current affairs
programme. Advertisements will be carried simultaneously on all four
options.
