FT  21 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: Germany look for win and second round
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
If they beat Spain today at Soldier Field, Chicago, defending champions
Germany could become the first of the 24 World Cup teams to advance to the
second round.
'We don't have a team that knows how to play for a draw,' said coach Berti
Vogts. 'We are an offensive team and that's how we'll play.' Vogts gave no
clue whether that meant a recall for veteran striker Rudi Voller.
Germany beat Bolivia 1-0 in the Group C opener last Friday, while Spain
wasted a 2-0 lead against South Korea, drawing 2-2. Worse for Spain was the
sending-off of captain Miguel Angel Nadal for an untimely tackle. Nadal was
later given a two-match suspension.
Spanish coach Javier Clemente has criticized Fifa, soccer's governing body,
for penalising Nadal more harshly than the usual one-match suspension. 'I
think it's totally unfair and out of proportion,' he said. 'I don't
understand it.'
