FT  21 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: Brazil dominate Russia in comfortable victory
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Rai hit the first penalty of the 1994 competition and Romario scored his
first World Cup finals goal as Brazil beat Russia 2-0 last night at Stanford
stadium near San Francisco.
Barcelona striker Romario turned in a corner from strike partner Bebeto in
the 27th minute and Rai fired home a spot kick in the 53rd after Romario had
been fouled.
A sellout crowd of 81,061 saw the Brazilians create many more chances in a
one-sided game in which Russia's goalkeeper, Dmitri Kharin of Chelsea, made
two stunning stops.
The Russians, depleted by the absence of overseas stars such as Manchester
United's Andrei Kanchelskis following a dispute with coach Pavel Sadyrin,
also had their captain, Viktor Onopko, missing through suspension.
Following their victory, Brazil were installed as 9-4 favourites to win the
tournament with both William Hill and Ladbrokes bookmakers.
