</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Air Uk is to operate four daily flights between Manchester and Amsterdam
from October 30 using a Fokker 100 in place of the KLM Boeing 737 now used
on the route.
KLM, which will continue to administer the service, believes the smaller
Fokker aircraft will be more economical.
