FT  20 JUN 94 / Business Travel: Welcome to Burma
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Burma's ruling military junta has launched a 'Visit Myanmar in 1996'
campaign in a bid to counter bad publicity abroad, according to state
television monitored in Thailand.
Myanmar, as the country is called by the military junta, has set itself the
ambitious target of attracting 600,000 tourists during 1996. Western
diplomats say there were fewer than 30,000 tourist arrivals in 1993.
