<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUN 94 / Business Travel: Children hurt
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Several children were injured when a coach taking them home from a church
outing lost control, police said today. The coach, carrying 31 children and
13 adults, ran across a roundabout and narrowly avoided two cars before
coming to a stop on a grassy bank on the A380 at the junction with the
Torbay ring road, Devon.
Some children were treated in hospital for shock before being released; one
12-year-old girl was detained overnight for observation.
</TEXT>
