<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUN 94 / Nissan personnel director to quit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Peter Wickens, personnel director of Nissan Motor Manufacturing (UK), is
to leave the company.
Mr Wickens, who is also a board member, is credited with moulding the shape
of industrial relations and practices at Nissan's Pounds 900m UK plant at
Sunderland, Tyne and Wear. He joined the Japanese carmaker in October 1984
as the first British employee of its Sunderland plant.
A former industrial-relations manager at Ford, he jettisoned most industrial
relations practices at Nissan, substituting team-working and flexibility.
He instituted a controversial single-union agreement with the AEEU
engineering union, as well as 'flat' management structures and single status
for all employees.
Last autumn he implemented an 'agreed separation' policy - shedding jobs
without redundancies. He will leave the company early next year.
</TEXT>
