<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: Colombia upset
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Romanian striker Florin Raducioiu scored one goal in each half as Romania
surprised Colombia 3-1 in a Group A game on Saturday in Los Angeles.
Colombia, rated by many as among the best of the 24 qualifiers, started well
but could not reassert themselves after going 2-0 down against a team that
counter-attacked furiously.
The US and Switzerland drew 1-1 in the weekend's other Group A game, at the
Silverdome in Pontiac, Michigan - the first World Cup match ever played
indoors. The game drew an overnight television rating of 5.8 points in the
US, beating the US Open Golf Championship.
The ABC television network, which carried the game, also said Sunday the
game produced an 18 share in a survey of 31 markets.
A ratings point represents 942,000 homes in the United States. The share is
the percentage of televisions tuned to the program at the time.
